However, neither of these works explicitly explores the interplay between curvature-aware precision routing and deterministic spectral estimators for training-free adaptive routing. This gap presents an opportunity to propose a novel approach that integrates these elements to enhance precision routing strategies in a training-free manner.

Proposal Refinement: I propose to refine the earlier idea by focusing on a curvature-aware precision routing framework that leverages deterministic spectral estimators to identify optimal precision tiers for different computational blocks. This approach will bridge geometric insights with practical deployment constraints, ensuring mathematical transparency and computational efficiency.

